Description.
Largest specimen complete, 12.92 mm long, 0.44 mm wide at chaetiger 10, with 52 chaetigers. Color in alcohol yellowish, anterior chaetigers reddish (
Fig. 33A
). Body cylindrical and thin; widths of prebranchial and branchial regions nearly same, becoming thinner on posterior region (
Fig. 33A
).

A dense dorsal ciliary band (dcb) present on mid-dorsal transversal line of each prebranchial and branchial chaetigers. A pair of short dorsal ciliary bands (sdcb) present just posterior to each branchial base (
Figs 34B
; 
35A
). Ciliary bands absent on ventral side of body.

Pygidium small and rounded, with three cirri (
Fig. 33F
); two cirri placed on dorsal side (long, digitiform, 37 μm long); one cirrus placed on ventral side (short, digitiform, 13 μm long).
